Matt Albar

Bio

Matt Albar is an industrial-organizational psychology practitioner. He is passionate about making the working experience better for everyone. He has a wide breadth of experience in HR functions, including recruitment, personnel selection, assessment, talent development, onboarding, compliance, compensation & benefits, and coaching. He partnered with many internal and external clients to conduct many different types of analyses to improve organizational processes.

Education

Montclair State University | Montclair, NJ

M.A. in Industrial-Organizational Psychology | September 2017 - May 2019

Drew University | Madison, NJ

B.A. in Psychology | September 2013 - May 2017

Experience

Spectrum | Talent Selection Analyst | September 2021 - Present

GAF | Agility Specialist | July 2019 - August 2021

Montclair State University | Graduate Intern, Assessment of Academic Programs and Strategic Planning | October 2018 - May 2019

BetterUp | Coach (Trial Program) | September 2018 - April 2019

Global Health Corps | Intern, People Team | May 2018 - September 2018

Jefferson County Commission | Assessor | May 2018
